public CrashReportData load(@NonNull

                                     JSONException
        Loads properties from the specified File.
        Parameters:

        CrashReportData read from the supplied File.

      • store

        public void store(@NonNull
                  CrashReportData crashData,
                  @NonNull
                  File file)
           throws IOException,
                  JSONException
        Stores the mappings in this Properties to the specified OutputStream, putting the specified comment at the beginning. The output from this method is suitable for being read by the load() method.
        Parameters:
        crashData - CrashReportData to save.
        file - File into which to store the CrashReportData.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the CrashReportData could not be written to the OutputStream.
        JSONException - if the crashData could not be converted to JSON.
